tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE printing_parameters (
  parameter_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  parameter_name VARCHAR(50),
  parameter_type VARCHAR(50),
  parameter_value FLOAT
)

CREATE TABLE materials_testing (
  test_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  material_name VARCHAR(50),
  test_result FLOAT,
  test_date DATE
)

CREATE TABLE performance_analysis (
  analysis_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  experiment_name VARCHAR(50),
  performance_score FLOAT
)

CREATE TABLE materials_testing_results (
   id INT PRIMARY KEY,
   material_name VARCHAR(50),
   test_date DATE,
   result_value FLOAT,
   tester_name VARCHAR(50)
);

CREATE TABLE performance_analysis (
   id INT PRIMARY KEY,
   analysis_date DATE,
   success_rate FLOAT,
   analysis_type VARCHAR(50),
   tester_name VARCHAR(50)
);

CREATE TABLE experimental_data (
   id INT PRIMARY KEY,
   experiment_date DATE,
   experiment_type VARCHAR(50),
   result_value FLOAT,
   researcher_name VARCHAR(50)
);

CREATE TABLE experiment_parameters (
  id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  parameter_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
  value FLOAT NOT NULL,
  timestamp TIMESTAMP
)

CREATE TABLE material_testing_results (
  id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  material_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
  test_result FLOAT NOT NULL,
  test_date DATE
)

CREATE TABLE performance_analysis (
  id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  test_id INT NOT NULL,
  performance_metric VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
  value FLOAT NOT NULL,
  timestamp TIMESTAMP
)
